reviewText:
Kingdoms of Amalur: Reckoning delivers exactly what it promises: a pitch-perfect fantasy RPG, with visceral, intuitive gameplay that is easy to pick up, difficult to master, wildly flexible and just plain fun, in a way that had previously not been seen in the genre.

{A General note. I pre-ordered this game when it first came out and thus played it on Origin, where I still have a copy owned.  I have three full playthroughs there each with over 130+ hours played, and one has mastercrafted equipment that made me literally invincible [unless I was afflicted with Bleed status]. And a forth playthrough done fast" with over seventy hours on it. So my time played stats here on steam should be added to those for Origin playtime of an additional 450+ hours.}

The world is accessible and vast

I only recommend this game if you're looking to give it as a Action RPG for young kids with age of 10+
Think on this game as the Disney version of Dragon Age.


Once you have understood my statement above these are the reasons why I recommend the game for that public
PROS:
- The game world is kinda big with lots (and I really mean LOTS) of side quests. Nowadays  a really cheap investment with hours of entertainment;
- The graphics are decent and the world was built charming enough to be considered a beautiful experience";
- The combat system was simplified enough to be considered a brawler;
- The level up/build system is nice so lots of combinations will be available (you can also reset them if needed);
- There are very simplified crafting and stealth system that will amuse the little nerds for hours;


CONS:
- In general the game is easy even on the hard difficult"

A great game for the time. Too bad this didn't develop into a serie.

+A well written story;
+Good fighting mechanics;
+Good character building;

-No permanent companions:
-Cannot bind mouse buttons;
-No romance options. :b

Solid 8/10

(Recommend to buy when on sale ;) )
